[
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we have a name for a group acting on another group that is compatible with the group structure?</p>",
        "id": 124835829,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523279134
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is this thing called G-module</p>",
        "id": 124836222,
        "sender_full_name": "jmc",
        "timestamp": 1523279942
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But then you act on abelian groups</p>",
        "id": 124836230,
        "sender_full_name": "jmc",
        "timestamp": 1523279953
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but a group is not a module</p>",
        "id": 124836231,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523279955
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>right</p>",
        "id": 124836232,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523279957
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Where does this show up?</p>",
        "id": 124836300,
        "sender_full_name": "jmc",
        "timestamp": 1523280093
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in my brain</p>",
        "id": 124836303,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523280103
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i'm just making this up</p>",
        "id": 124836304,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523280110
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh wait, this does show up in group theory</p>",
        "id": 124836308,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523280120
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>a group acts on a normal subgroup by conjugation</p>",
        "id": 124836348,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523280127
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, G-modules show up a lot in group cohomology</p>",
        "id": 124836349,
        "sender_full_name": "jmc",
        "timestamp": 1523280128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Aah, ok, sure</p>",
        "id": 124836351,
        "sender_full_name": "jmc",
        "timestamp": 1523280139
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>right, i'm learning group cohomology right now</p>",
        "id": 124836352,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523280140
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and then an action of G on N is just a homomorphism G -&gt; Aut(N)</p>",
        "id": 124836355,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1523280157
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure, but if G acts on G', it is also just a homom G -&gt; Aut(G')</p>",
        "id": 124836366,
        "sender_full_name": "jmc",
        "timestamp": 1523280207
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if the action is compatible with the group structure</p>",
        "id": 124836370,
        "sender_full_name": "jmc",
        "timestamp": 1523280228
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If the group M you're acting on is abelian, then this is just called a G-module usually (G the group doing the acting)</p>",
        "id": 124836498,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1523280472
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If M is not abelian then this is sometimes called a \"non-abelian G-module\" and the theory very quickly gets technical</p>",
        "id": 124836539,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1523280488
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>H^1 is no longer a group, but just a pointed set</p>",
        "id": 124836549,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1523280509
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and for higher cohomology groups one has to use fancy stuff like gerbes</p>",
        "id": 124836557,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1523280530
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See Serre's book on Galois cohomology (some appendix) for a brief and clear introduction.</p>",
        "id": 124836577,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1523280577
    }
]